## Candidates

- `managed`: score `85` rejection `none`
  - hot-inode skew favors centralized backpressure
  - write-heavy fsync cadence favors managed scheduling
- `per_core`: score `50` rejection `none`
  - CPU/RAM/NUMA floor can support per-core routing
